<TITLE> France's Ribery has sprained ankle and knee injury </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 VEVEY, Switzerland, June 18 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - France playmaker Franck Ribery sprained his left ankle and hurt his knee in the 2-0 defeat by Italy at Euro 2008, coach Raymond Domenech said on Wednesday. "He has a nasty ankle sprain," Domenech told a news conference. "As for the knee, we're not quite sure yet how serious the injury is. Further checks are needed. "He's walking on crutches, he can't put his foot down," Domenech added. Ribery injured his left leg falling heavily following a push on Gianluca Zambrotta and was carried off on a stretcher 10 minutes into the Group C game in Zurich on Tuesday. Italy qualified for the quarter-finals while France were eliminated
